Edward MACEY, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 6540. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 15, 1932. Edward Macey, in pro. per. Glint W. Hager, U. S. Attys., and Hal Lindsay, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and WALK- . ER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
